# Use the default Docker configuration location as ID.
# This will save provided credentials to `/root/.docker/config.json`.
# If you specify a user id to run the container, the default Docker configuration location will change. You may use environment variable `DOCKER_CONFIG` to explicitly set the default location.
/root/.docker default_registry.com default_username default_password
# You can save multiple credentials in the same configuration, yet registries must be different.
# Assuming that Docker allows to store credentials of different registries into a single client configuration.
/root/.docker 3rd_registry.com 3rd_username 3rd_password
/root/.docker 4th_registry.com 4th_username 4th_password
